Population growth model table for Johnson models

Source: R/popGrowthTableJohnsonECCC.R
popGrowthTableJohnsonECCC.Rd

A table of population growth model coefficients and standard errors or confidence intervals for the models described in Johnson et. al. (2020)

popGrowthTableJohnsonECCC

Format

An object of class data.frame with 27 rows and 9 columns.

References

Johnson, C.A., Sutherland, G.D., Neave, E., Leblond, M., Kirby, P., Superbie, C. and McLoughlin, P.D., 2020. Science to inform policy: linking population dynamics to habitat for a threatened species in Canada. Journal of Applied Ecology, 57(7), pp.1314-1327. https://doi.org/10.1111/1365-2664.13637
